fields.text: If you are not sure how to spell a word, you;

options.text: spell it out loud or in your head
you write it down until it looks right
you draw it in the air with your finger

fields.text: When you see the word "cat," what do you do first?

options.text: Picture a cat in your mind
Say the word "cat" to yourself
Think about being with a cat (petting it or hearing it purr)

fields.text: I am good at taking tests
I like a professor with firm due dates

options.text: Get someone to show you
Read about it or listen to someone explain it
Figure it out on your own

fields.text: When in a new place, how do you find your way around?

options.text: Look for a map or directory that shows you where everything is
Ask someone for directions
Just start walking around until you find what you're looking for

fields.text: When you hear a song on the radio, what are you most likely to do?

options.text: Sing or hum along with the music
Start dancing or tapping your foot
Picture the video that goes along with it

fields.text: I am a heavy note taker

options.text: Picture the numbers on the phone as you would dial them
Say it out loud over and over
Try to write it down

fields.text: Which would you rather go to with a group of friends?

options.text: A movie
A concert
An amusement park

fields.text: I feel as though I am "smarter" than my classmates

options.text: Their face but not their name
Their name but not their face
What you talked about with them

I like to work in groups
I am very organized

options.text: I end up doing most of the work

options.text: Quiet and stick with my close friends

The center of attention
By myself

options.text: repetition or mnemonics eg. PEMDAS
flashcards
making detailed notes with diagrams

fields.text: I learn best when I am shown how to do something, and I have the opportunity to do it.

options.text: Someone with a lot of money
